# Altitutor Monorepo Overview

## Project Structure

This is a pnpm-based Turborepo monorepo with three Next.js applications:
- `apps/admin-web`: Admin CRM system (port 3000)
- `apps/student-web`: Student-facing portal (port 3001)
- `apps/tutor-web`: Tutor-facing portal (port 3002)
- `packages/shared`: Shared types and utilities
- `packages/ui`: Shared UI components

## Feature-First Architecture

Each application follows **feature-first architecture**:
- Organize by feature (e.g., `features/students/`, `features/billing/`)
- Colocate components, hooks, API calls, types, and mappers within features
- Structure:
  ```
  features/
    [feature-name]/
      api/           # API client functions
      components/    # Feature-specific components
      hooks/         # React Query hooks and custom hooks
      types/         # TypeScript types
      mappers/       # Data transformation functions
      index.ts       # Public exports
  ```

## Separation of Concerns

- **Never mix business logic with UI components**
- Extract business logic to:
  - Custom hooks (for stateful logic)
  - Utility functions (for pure transformations)
  - Service/API layer (for data fetching)
- Components should focus on rendering and user interaction
- Keep components small and focused (< 200 lines ideally)

## File Naming Conventions

- React components: PascalCase (e.g., `StudentTable.tsx`)
- Utilities, hooks: camelCase (e.g., `useStudents.ts`, `formatDate.ts`)
- Types/interfaces: PascalCase (e.g., `StudentProfile.ts`)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE in files named `constants.ts`
